      "file": "app/globals.css",
      "root_cause": "Registered the custom font token self-referentially: `@theme inline { --font-georgia: var(--font-georgia); }` with the real value only in `:root`. Tailwind v4 resolves a theme token's value to decide whether to emit a `font-*` utility; a self-referential `var(--font-georgia)` resolves as circular/empty, so Tailwind dropped it and produced NO `.font-georgia` rule. This trick works for `--font-sans: var(--font-sans)` ONLY because `font-sans` is a built-in Tailwind utility that exists regardless of the theme value — it does NOT create a novel utility name.",
      "fix": "Give the `@theme inline` token a concrete value referencing the next/font/local variable: `@theme inline { --font-georgia: var(--font-georgia-base), Georgia, serif; }` and remove the redundant `:root --font-georgia`. Verified the served CSS chunk now contains `.font-georgia { font-family: var(--font-georgia-base), Georgia, serif; }`. `--font-georgia-base` is set on <html> by next/font/local (4 Georgia ttf variants).",
      "tags": [
        "tailwind-v4",
        "theme-inline",
        "font-family",
